Scottish independent schools have improved academic achievements record by not losing track of 2018 and have again demonstrated outstanding exam results, which have only been further enhanced by individual and collective achievements in sports, art, music and other community achievements.
When more than 30 000 pupils are enrolled in all Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Independent School Council (SCIS), aim to provide the highest possible level of service to their students and their parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare their students for further and higher education, for their chosen career and to be citizens of the world.
