According to the results of this year's recent exams, languages are on the top of popularity and have the best maintenance ratings in independent schools.
In total, 68 percent of students who learned a foreign language received the highest A rating.
Data collected from 74 schools that are members of the SCIS showed that 72 percent of students received the highest A rating during the Mandarin examination, 72 percent of those who studied German, and 69 percent of those who studied French and 63 percent of those who studied Spanish.
